        "title": "Update to Elite Device Labelling and Instructions for Use",
        "description": "<p>We are reaching out to share an important update regarding the labelling and Instructions for Use (IFU) for certain Elite devices purchased between 22 April 2022 and 13 August 2024. </p><p> </p><p><strong>What is the update? </strong> </p><p>The Hydrafacial Elite device is available in two versions—one classified as a medical device and one as a non-medical device. <strong>The device itself remains exactly the same </strong>in design, performance, and functionality. The only difference lies in the intended use and the accompanying labelling/IFU. </p><p> </p><p>During a recent review, we identified that some devices were shipped with labelling that did not reflect the correct intended-use version (non-medical). To ensure documentation is aligned with the appropriate regulatory classification, we are providing updated labelling and IFUs for your device. </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Does this affect device safety or performance?</strong> </p><p><strong>No</strong>. There are <strong>no modifications</strong> to your device. We have <strong>received no reports</strong> of adverse effects, malfunctions, or safety concerns related to this matter. This update is <strong>purely administrative </strong>to ensure your accompanying documentation accurately reflects the device’s qualification as a non-medical device. </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>What do you need to do?</strong> </p><p>Please take a moment to: </p><p>-  Replace the current IFU with the updated version provided, see below for instructions.</p><p>- Apply the enclosed updated labels. </p><p>- Fill out  the following form: </p>",
        "id_number": 1
      }
